const faqs = [
  { q: "Who owns Maytag Commercial?", a: "Maytag Commercial Laundry is a division of Whirlpool Corporation, headquartered in Benton Harbor, Michigan. Whirlpool acquired Maytag in 2006, folding the commercial laundry line into the Whirlpool Corporation portfolio alongside Whirlpool-branded commercial, KitchenAid residential, JennAir, Amana, and Roper. Since 2006, the Maytag Commercial division has shared engineering lineage + parts distribution + dealer network with Whirlpool Commercial — the two lines are siblings under the Whirlpool Corp umbrella, differentiated more by badge and product-tier positioning than by fundamental engineering. For LA operators running mixed Whirlpool + Maytag installations, the Whirlpool Corp parts-chain advantage is real: Whirlpool has extensive LA-area parts warehouse infrastructure, supporting same-day or 1-day delivery on most common service components." },
  { q: "Maytag Commercial vs Maytag residential — different product lines?", a: "Yes — same Whirlpool Corp parent, different product lines with different parts. Maytag Commercial (MAH top-load, MDG/MDE dryers, MLG multi-load, MVWC/MVWP multi-voltage coin-op) is specified for laundromat + apartment laundry-room + small OPL duty cycles. Maytag residential (MVW top-load, MED electric dryer, MGD gas dryer series at the residential tier) is home-use consumer equipment with residential duty-cycle parts. The parts don't cross over in most components — a Maytag Commercial MAH coin-op drive belt doesn't fit a Maytag residential MVW top-load. If you're calling about Maytag service, let dispatch know whether it's commercial (coin-op, laundromat, apartment room, OPL) or residential (home use) so the right parts go on the truck. Residential Maytag service runs at the $89 residential diagnostic tier; this commercial combo page is the $120 commercial scope." },
  { q: "Maytag MAH coin-op vs Speed Queen LTSA — which is more common in LA laundromats?", a: "Speed Queen LTSA dominates LA laundromat specification — it's the default for new laundromat builds and most chain-acquisition conversions. Maytag Commercial MAH turns up at mid-tier laundromats as an alternative specification, particularly in older operator-owned laundromats acquired pre-2010 before the current Alliance dominance was fully established. Maytag's current LA laundromat share is smaller than Alliance but meaningful — probably 15–25% of coin-op top-load install base across the LA basin. The Whirlpool Corp parts-chain advantage is the operational value: Maytag MAH parts are faster to source in LA than some Alliance specialty parts (Whirlpool's LA warehouse density is higher). For laundromats replacing a failing MAH unit, the choice between matching with more MAH or transitioning to Speed Queen LTSA is a real trade-off — we don't push one over the other; we service what's installed." },
  { q: "What does Maytag Commercial repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical Maytag Commercial service ranges: coin mechanism cleaning + realignment $180–$320, door interlock $200–$340, drive belt replacement $200–$340, water-inlet valve $220–$380, door gasket $220–$380, coin slide replacement $240–$420, drain pump $260–$440, main motor service $380–$620, control board $650–$1,100, MDG/MDE dryer gas valve $300–$500, MDG/MDE dryer ignitor + flame sensor $240–$400, full drum-bearing rebuild $600–$1,000. Most Maytag Commercial calls land $260–$520 parts-and-labor. Coin-op mechanism work and bearing rebuilds run at the higher end. See our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-dryer-repair-cost/\">commercial dryer repair cost guide</a>." },
  { q: "Do you service Whirlpool + Maytag Commercial in the same call?", a: "Yes — Whirlpool Commercial and Maytag Commercial are the same Whirlpool Corp parts chain, and mixed rooms are common. We routinely service rooms running Whirlpool CAE + Maytag MAH + occasional Whirlpool MVWB multi-voltage on one dispatch. The parts truck is the same (Whirlpool Corp parts cover both brands), and diagnostic logic parallels between the two lines. For LA property managers running Whirlpool Corp-family laundry rooms (apartment buildings, laundromats, small OPL), this is a real operational convenience vs juggling separate service providers for each brand." }
];

