  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Maytag Commercial — Whirlpool Corp division since 2006</h2>
    <p>Maytag Commercial Laundry has been a division of Whirlpool Corporation since 2006, when Whirlpool acquired the Maytag company and folded the commercial laundry line into its broader Benton Harbor MI portfolio. Whirlpool Corp's portfolio now includes Whirlpool Commercial (sibling commercial laundry brand), KitchenAid residential, JennAir, Amana, Roper, Gladiator, and the Maytag line itself spanning residential + commercial. For LA operators running any Whirlpool Corp equipment, the shared parts distribution infrastructure is the operational value — Whirlpool's LA warehouse network is denser than most competing brands, translating to same-day or 1-day delivery on most common service components.</p>
    <p>In the US commercial laundry landscape, Maytag Commercial occupies a mid-tier position. It's neither the Alliance Speed Queen / Huebsch dominance spec nor the industrial Milnor / ADC tier — it fills the operational slot for laundromats choosing alternative specification, apartment building laundry rooms where Whirlpool Corp parts-chain is the decisive factor, and small-format OPL (smaller hotels, mid-size apartment-complex laundry rooms) where Maytag's build quality meets the duty-cycle requirement without the premium over Alliance Speed Queen Commercial.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Maytag Commercial models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MAH — coin-op top-load flagship</h3><p>Maytag's coin-op top-load laundromat flagship. LA install base concentrates in older operator-owned laundromats and mid-tier laundromat chains. Service: coin mechanism, door interlock, drive belt, water-inlet valve, drain pump.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MDG / MDE — gas / electric dryers</h3><p>Commercial single-pocket dryers. MDG (gas) and MDE (electric) variants across capacity tiers. Apartment laundry + laundromat standard. Service: burner + ignitor + gas valve (MDG); heating element (MDE); door switch, belt, drum rollers, lint filter pressure switch.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MLG / MLE — multi-load washers</h3><p>Multi-load commercial washers (higher capacity than MAH). Small OPL + apartment laundry room configurations. Service pattern parallels MAH at larger scale.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>MVWC / MVWP — multi-voltage commercial</h3><p>Multi-voltage commercial washers designed for installations with non-standard electrical service. Apartment conversions + older LA buildings with legacy electrical often require multi-voltage spec. Service: standard commercial washer components + voltage-mode switching.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Coin mechanism + card-reader integration</h3><p>Maytag Commercial coin-variants interface with similar card-reader systems as Speed Queen (ESD, Card Concepts). We service the mechanical side; card-system integration is coordinated with the card vendor.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Dependability 10-year warranty context</h3><p>Maytag Commercial's Dependability 10-year limited warranty badge has been a brand-signature since the 1960s. Out-of-warranty repair work sometimes draws from Whirlpool Corp's extended-service network; we coordinate with the warranty channel where the unit is still covered.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Whirlpool + Maytag single-call — the LA property-management angle</h2>
    <p>Property managers running multi-building apartment complexes, medium-scale laundromats, and small OPL across LA County often have mixed Whirlpool Commercial + Maytag Commercial laundry rooms. The two brands share Whirlpool Corp's parts chain and dealer network completely — a service provider stocking parts for one line stocks parts for the other. Our LA coverage handles these rooms on single dispatches routinely; one call, one tech, all brands covered.</p>
    <p>Specific LA verticals where we see this pattern: Koreatown + Mid-Wilshire + East LA apartment complexes with in-building laundry rooms (Whirlpool Corp family dominates here historically); smaller independent laundromats across South LA + Pico-Union; fitness-center + small-hotel OPL where Whirlpool Corp was specified rather than Alliance; legacy apartment rooms built before 2010 that haven't been converted to newer Alliance spec.</p>
    <p>Cross-brand service dispatch is also useful at mixed Alliance + Whirlpool Corp rooms. LA laundromat operators who've bought out multiple properties over the years frequently inherit mixed rooms — we handle both Alliance (Speed Queen/UniMac/Huebsch) and Whirlpool Corp (Whirlpool Commercial/Maytag Commercial) on one call rather than forcing the operator to juggle separate providers.</p>
  </div></section>

